parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system fan clutch can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The premature failure of the radiator can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The design flaw of the radiator cap can cause burn injuries to the consumer when removing the cap, and can also lead to engine overheating and damage.
The leaks in the engine cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The defective tail light sockets can cause the tail lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Tail lights blink on and off
tail lights do not stay on consistently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor design of the headlight assembly can lead to excessive repair costs and increased risk of accidents due to prolonged periods of reduced visibility.
symptoms: Broken headlight requires removal of entire grill for repair
